    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nCannot enter the pager  if `<ESC>` is remapped to `:fclose`:\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: ...rc-dev/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua:607: Invalid window id: 1004\nstack traceback:\n\t[C]: in function 'nvim_win_get_height'\n\t...rc-dev/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua:607: in function <...rc-dev/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/_core/ui2/messages.lua:606>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean --cmd \"lua require('vim._core.ui2').enable({msg = {target = 'msg'}})\" --cmd 'nmap <Esc> <Cmd>fclose<CR>'`\n- type `:hi<CR><CR>`.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo error.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.13.0-dev-359+g72bc6c5801\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\n alacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
